cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper presents a dynamic artificial neural network-based adaptive inference process for learning temporal predictive models of dynamical systems. The paper focuses on the development of a monolithic neural event inference architecture that can learn planning and control. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for learning temporal predictive models, which makes it relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for learning temporal forward models, which is a common technique in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper discusses the use of the learned model for inducing goal-directed, model-predictive control, which is relevant to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the developed architecture for maintaining model coherence, which is relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
